<!DOCTYPE html>
{{>copyright }}

<html lang="en">

<head>

  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>GC API v1</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/img/spx-gc.ico">

  <style>

    body {
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background-color: rgb(223, 223, 223);
      padding: 1em;
    }

    a:link {
      font-family: monospace;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 1.2em;
      background-color: #eee;
      font-weight: bold;
      padding: 0.2em 0.2em;
    }

    a:hover {
      background-color: rgb(255, 248, 189);
    }

    h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    p {
      margin-top: 0.2em;
    }


    .auto-resizable-iframe {
      max-width: 100%;
      margin: 0px auto;
    }
  </style>
</head>


<body class="bg_body">
  <H1>API v1</H1>
  <B>http/get</B> commands available for external systems to trigger SPX-GC events.
  <BR>
  SPX-GC will need to be open in a browser (in the same network as the server) for most of these to work.
  <BR><BR>
  <small>Remember, SPX-GC is primarily targeted to live, manually operated
  workflows and API does not currently allow for modification of template
  data or other advanced procedures.</small>
  <BR>


  {{#each functionList.sections}}
    <BR>
    <h3>{{section}}</h3>
    <p>{{info}}</p>
    {{#each commands}}
      <A HREF="http://{{{getServerAddress}}}{{../endpoint}}{{param}}">http://{{{getServerAddress}}}{{../endpoint}}{{param}}</A><BR>
      <p>{{info}}</p>
    {{/each}}
  {{/each}}

</body>
</html>